gomodel:SYNGO_224  a      owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: CTTNBP2 interacts with the actin-binding protein cortactin (CTTN; SynGo ID 223) and is localized in dendritic spines, co-localizing with PSD-95 and F-actin.\n\n9/3/2017 Pim:\n-literal; \"Together, these immunofluorescence experiments identified the synaptic distribution of CTTNBP2 in cultured neurons and mouse brains and suggested an association of CTTNBP2 with actin cytoskeletons.\". Experimental description: from the figure legend: \"Immunohistochemistry of adult mouse hippocampus with CTTNBP2 antibody\" (Figure 3). Also, shows dendritic spine localization in rat hippocampal neurons.\n\n9/3/2017 Pim:\n-species of cultured neurons (Fig.3A-D) is **rat**.\n-species of brain slices (Fig.3E) is **mouse**.\n-Species of the myc-tagged over-expressed CTTNBP2 proteins is **mouse** since cloned from RIKEN sequence RIKEN 4732477G22 and IMAGE 6833056.\n-Final annotation made against **mouse**" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-6153-3586" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2666-0758" ;
        dc:date           "2017-03-21" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_224" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

